<TITLE> Govt makes DPS income tax-free </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 29 (bdnews24.com)Income from interests on deposit pension schemes (DPS) has been made tax-free, according to a decision made by the cabinet Sunday. It means no income tax will be deducted at source from the interest or profit subscribers earn on their DPS. At a meeting at the Chief Adviser's Office, the cabinet amended the Income Tax Ordinance. Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed presided over the meeting. National Board of Revenue chairman Muhammad Abdul Mazid told bdnews24.com Sunday: "The government has decided to make the income from DPS tax-free to encourage savings." "Tax had earlier been deducted at source on DPS income." bdnews
